SIMPLE: crampet
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Crampet
<hw>Cram"pet</hw> <pr>(kr?m"p?t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Cramp</er>,<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A
cramp iron or cramp ring; a chape, as of a scabbard.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>crampit</asp> and
<asp>crampette</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One of the plates of iron, with attached spikes,
forming a pair of crampoons</def>; <specif>hence</specif>
<fld>(Curling)</fld>, <def>an iron plate for a player to stand on when
delivering the stones.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crampfish</ent>⟦br⟧
